text: Burleigh County is a county located in the U.S. state of North Dakota. As of the 2020 census, the population was 98,458. It is the second-most populous county in North Dakota. Its county seat is Bismarck. The county was created on January 4, 1873 and later organized on July 16. ==References== Category:North Dakota counties
title: Burleigh County, North Dakota
